      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. could you add a little more warmth to it though? like, maybe something that emphasizes how much we genuinely appreciated their time and how much the team enjoyed meeting them, without sounding like we're making excuses for the decision. just a bit more \"human\" feeling?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can certainly add more warmth to that email to make it feel more human and appreciative, while still keeping the decision clear. I will ensure the tone is genuine and empathetic, acknowledging the strength of the candidate without over-explaining the hiring process.\n\n**Revised Draft Email:**\n\nSubject: Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position in Austin. We genuinely enjoyed meeting you and hearing about your passion for system design; it was a real pleasure having you in the room.\n\nWhile you were a standout candidate, especially regarding your culture fit and technical depth, we ultimately decided to move forward with a candidate who has a bit more hands-on experience with our specific cloud stack. We wanted to be transparent about this, as we want to ensure the person we hire can hit the ground running.\n\nPlease know that we truly appreciate your time and energy. We were genuinely impressed by you, and we hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]",
